  <front>
   <head>MARTIAL, Book IV. Ep. 87.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WOu'dst thou, by Attic taste approv'd,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">By all be read, by all be lov'd,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To learned Harris' curious eye,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">By me advis'd, dear Muse, apply:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In him the perfect judge you'll find,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In him the candid friend, and kind.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If he repeats, if he approves,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If he the laughing muscles moves,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thou nor the critic's sneer shal'st mind,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor be to pie's or trunks consign'd.</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If he condemns, away you fly,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And mount in paper kites the sky,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or dead 'mongst Grub-street's records lye.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
